name: Plymouth Public Health

tweet: Plastics in the ocean pose a threat to the public’s health and environment. Keep Plymouth Beautiful is taking action to address the issue. You can get involved with their beach cleanup at Center Hill Preserve on June 15th 1pm:  https://t.co/jWvlRyBrCn

name: Plymouth Public Health
tweet: Our first Public Health and Board of Health Strategic Plan and Roadmap is available. It’s was made with the public for the public. It’s our guiding document for 2019-2022. Access it here:  https://t.co/dPI9gwOU7p

name: Plymouth Public Health
tweet: Hey folks ! The Plymouth Area MRC is looking for volunteers to join a national network committed to improving the health, safety, and resiliency of their community! Stop by and see us!  https://t.co/lmTcTFALPs

name: Plymouth Public Health
tweet: We are being proactive regarding the re-emergence of measles in the US and internationally. Please review our Public Health Advisory to help protect the health of Plymouth residents and visitors. Click for more details and our official guidance:  https://t.co/fvTFxiOP4P

name: Plymouth Public Health
tweet: One of our many community health collaborators, The Wildlands Trust will host a 3-part climate change speaking series beginning on April 22 with “The Psychology of Climate Change” presented by Dr. Jacob Nato from The Harvard Medical School. For more info:  https://t.co/mxK3Iz5J4U

name: Plymouth Public Health
tweet: @carains and our organization are happy to announce that we were awarded a Mass-DPH Comprehensive School Health Services Grant. We will work to improve adolescent health in the @PlymouthSch school system and also the community....in a comprehensive fashion. More details to come!

tweet: Board of Health Regulatory Update: The Select Board approved the 2019 Board of Health Fee and Fine structure on 8 Jan, 2019. The revised fees and fines will be officially implemented start 10 Jan, 2019. The new Fee and Fine schedule can be found here:  https://t.co/ORLCFpHeA8

name: Plymouth Public Health
tweet: ATTN - On Jan. 9th, 7pm during the Board of Health meeting in the Town Hall's Ropewalk Meeting room: The Honorable MA State Rep. Matt Muratore will speak about affordable housing and engaging in discussion about its connection with public's health and healthcare costs.

name: Plymouth Public Health
tweet: Currently, we are crowd sourcing input to determine what Plymouthians would like to see regarding optimal public health in and across the Town of Plymouth. This takes no more than 2 minutes for you to complete:  https://t.co/GIG7zzI9X1

name: Plymouth Public Health
tweet: 21 is 21 in Plymouth: As of today the sale of all tobacco products (including e-cigs and vape products) is 21 and older. No grandfathering of ages. For more local regulatory specifics click the following link:  https://t.co/Xa3NVSP7VV

name: Plymouth Public Health
tweet: We are pleased to announce our new Fats, Oil, and Grease (FOG) Guidelines and Manual for Food Establishments is available! Food establishment owners, staff, and stakeholders can access it on the  https://t.co/R2OQxBwTkE website or directly here:  https://t.co/n2IjqFE8ea

name: Plymouth Public Health
tweet: Community collaboration across policing, public health, healthcare, and other community health partners to further address the opioid epidemic is demonstrating its effectiveness through the Plymouth County Outreach Program at the community level. #sustainablechange

name: Plymouth Public Health
tweet: As a reminder, Tobacco sales (inclusive of vaping products) will be set at the age of 21 effective December 28, 2018. -No Grandfathering will be allowed in Plymouth- For more info visit:  https://t.co/MQ5c2inIjP

name: Plymouth Public Health
tweet: The @CDC is advising all US consumers to not eat any romaine lettuce, and retailers and restaurants to not serve or sell it due to a current multi-state e.coli outbreak. More info will be provided via @CDC as it becomes available.
